title: Seed data for projects
description: Implement `app/seed/projects.py` with async seed_projects(session, users_dict) function. Create 6 projects matching prototype: 1) AI Resume Builder (Maya, SHIPPED, React/Python/OpenAI/PostgreSQL, 1200 users, 340 stars), 2) Tribe Finder (Maya owner + Priya collab, IN_PROGRESS, Next.js/Go/PostgreSQL), 3) Open Source CRM (David, IN_PROGRESS, React/Node.js/PostgreSQL, 89 stars), 4) Design System Kit (James, SHIPPED, Figma/React/Storybook, 520 stars), 5) ML Pipeline Framework (Sarah, SHIPPED, Python/TensorFlow/Docker, 2100 stars), 6) Growth Analytics Dashboard (David owner + Elena collab, IN_PROGRESS, Next.js/Python/Grafana). Create ProjectCollaborator records with CONFIRMED status for collaborations. Include title, description, tech_stack, impact_metrics, github_stars. Return project dict.
acceptance_criteria:
- Exactly 6 projects created
- All fields match spec (titles, tech stacks, statuses, stars)
- ProjectCollaborator records for: Maya+Priya, David+Elena
- Collaborator status = CONFIRMED
- impact_metrics JSONB populated for shipped projects
- github_stars match: 340, 89, 520, 2100
- Returns project dict
